103 Therefore we speak and therefore we laugh;
104 therefore we produce the tears and sighs
105 that you could have heard throughout the mountain.

106 Depending on how desires and
107 other emotions afflict us, the shade takes shape;
108 and this is the reason for what you see."

112 Here the bank shoots out flames,
113 and the cornice blows a breath upwards
114 that reflects it and separates it from itself;

121 Then I heard 'Summae Deus clementiae' sung
122 in the midst of the great heat,
123 which made me no less eager to turn;

124 and I saw spirits walking through the flames;
125 so I looked at them and at my steps,
126 dividing my attention from time to time.

127 Near the end of that hymn,
